Q6 What is prop drilling?

Prop drilling is passing props from a parent to a deeply nested child
through multiple components that don’t actually use the data.

Simple & Short Prop Drilling Example

App → Child → GrandChild

App.jsx
function App() {
  const name = "Ganesh";
  return <Child name={name} />;
}
Child.jsx (does NOT use name ❗)
function Child({ name }) {
  return <GrandChild name={name} />;
}
GrandChild.jsx (actual usage)
function GrandChild({ name }) {
  return <h1>Hello {name}</h1>;
}


